quran[51]{c,v,t}:
  26,1,Ta Sin Mim
  26,2,Those are the signs of the Manifest Book
  26,3,Perchance thou consumest thyself that they are not believers
  26,4,"If We will, We shall send down on them out of heaven a sign, so their necks will stay humbled to it"
  26,5,"But never fresh remembrance comes to them from the All-merciful, except they turn away from it"
  26,6,So they have cried lies; therefore assuredly tidings will come to them of that they mocked at
  26,7,"What, have they not regarded the earth, how many therein We have caused to grow of every generous kind"
  26,8,"Surely in that is a sign, yet most of them are not believers"
  26,9,"Surely thy Lord, He is the All-mighty, the All-compassionate"
  26,10,"And when thy Lord called to Moses, 'Go to the people of the evildoers"
  26,11,the people of Pharaoh; will they not be godfearing
  26,12,"He said, 'My Lord, I fear they will cry me lies"
  26,13,"and my breast will be straitened, and my tongue will not be loosed; so send to Aaron"
  26,14,"They also have a sin against me, and I fear they will slay me"
  26,15,"Said He, 'No indeed; but go, both of you, with Our signs, and We assuredly shall be with you, listening"
  26,16,"So go you to Pharaoh, and say, \"Verily, I am the Messenger of the Lord of all Being"
  26,17,so send forth with us the Children of Israel
  26,18,"He said, 'Did we not raise thee amongst us as a child? Didst thou not tarry among us years of thy life"
  26,19,"And thou didst the deed thou didst, being one of the ungrateful"
  26,20,"Said he, 'Indeed I did it then, being one of those that stray"
  26,21,"so I fled from you, fearing you. But my Lord gave me Judgment and made me one of the Envoys"
  26,22,"That is a blessing thou reproachest me with, having enslaved the Children of Israel"
  26,23,"Pharaoh said, 'And what is the Lord of all Being"
  26,24,"He said, 'The Lord of the heavens and earth, and what between them is, if you have faith"
  26,25,"Said he to those about him, 'Do you not hear"
  26,26,"He said, 'Your Lord and the Lord of your fathers, the ancients"
  26,27,"Said he, 'Surely your Messenger who was sent to you is possessed"
  26,28,"He said, 'The Lord of the East and West, and what between them is, if you have understanding"
  26,29,"Said he, 'If thou takest a god other than me, I shall surely make thee one of the imprisoned"
  26,30,"He said, 'What, even though I brought thee something so manifest"
  26,31,"Said he, 'Bring it then, if thou art of the truthful"
  26,32,"So he cast his staff, and behold, it was a serpent manifest"
  26,33,"And he drew forth his hand, and lo, it was white to the beholders"
  26,34,"Said he to the Council about him, 'Surely this man is a cunning sorcerer"
  26,35,who desires to expel you from your land by his sorcery; what do you command
  26,36,"They said, 'Put him and his brother off a while, and send among the cities musterers"
  26,37,to bring thee every cunning sorcerer
  26,38,So the sorcerers were assembled for the appointed time of a fixed day
  26,39,"The people were asked, 'Will you assemble"
  26,40,Haply we shall follow the sorcerers if it should be they are the victors
  26,41,"Then, when the sorcerers came, they said to Pharaoh, 'Shall we indeed have a wage, if we should be the victors"
  26,42,"He said, 'Yes indeed; and you shall then be among the near-stationed"
  26,43,"Moses said to them, 'Cast you down what you will cast"
  26,44,"So they cast their ropes and their staffs, and said, 'By the might of Pharaoh we shall be the victors"
  26,45,"Then Moses cast his staff and lo, it forthwith swallowed up their lying invention"
  26,46,"so the sorcerers were cast down, bowing themselves"
  26,47,"They said, 'We believe in the Lord of all Being"
  26,48,the Lord of Moses and Aaron
  26,49,"Said Pharaoh, 'You have believed him before I gave you leave. Why, he is the chief of you, the same that taught you sorcery; now you shall know! I shall assuredly cut off alternately your hands and feet, then I shall crucify you all together"
  26,50,"They said, 'There is no harm; surely unto our Lord we are turning"
  26,51,"We are eager that our Lord should forgive us our offences, for that we are the first of the believers"